(a) Host a Simple Flask Web Application (Theoretical) 

Steps 

1. Install Flask on Raspberry Pi using the terminal. 
pip3 install flask 
2. Create a Python file named app.py. 
3. Write a Flask application that hosts a simple webpage. 
4. Run the Flask server using the terminal. 
python3 app.py 
5. Open a web browser and access the web application. 
http://<RaspberryPi-IP>:5000

Code (Flask Web Server) 

from flask import Flask 
 
app = Flask(__name__) 
 
@app.route('/') 
def home(): 
    return "Welcome to Raspberry Pi Web Server" 
 
if __name__ == '__main__': 
    app.run(host='0.0.0.0', port=5000) 

Expected Output 
When the browser accesses the server: 
Welcome to Raspberry Pi Web Server 
This confirms that the Flask web server is running successfully. 


(b) Control LEDs via Buttons on a Webpage (Theoretical) 
Connection 
Component     Raspberry Pi 
LED 1         GPIO17 
LED 2         GPIO18 
LED Cathode   GND

Steps 
1. Connect LEDs to Raspberry Pi GPIO pins. 
2. Create a Flask application that includes LED control routes. 
3. Design a webpage with ON and OFF buttons. 
4. When a button is pressed, the Flask route changes the GPIO output state.

CODE

from flask import Flask, render_template 
import RPi.GPIO as GPIO 
 
GPIO.setmode(GPIO.BCM) 
 
LED1 = 17 
LED2 = 18 
 
GPIO.setup(LED1, GPIO.OUT) 
GPIO.setup(LED2, GPIO.OUT) 
 
app = Flask(__name__) 
 
@app.route('/') 
def index(): 
    return ''' 
    <h2>LED Control</h2> 
    <a href="/led1_on"><button>LED1 ON</button></a> 
    <a href="/led1_off"><button>LED1 OFF</button></a><br><br> 
    <a href="/led2_on"><button>LED2 ON</button></a> 
    <a href="/led2_off"><button>LED2 OFF</button></a> 
    ''' 
 
@app.route('/led1_on') 
def led1_on(): 
    GPIO.output(LED1, True) 
    return "LED1 Turned ON" 
 
@app.route('/led1_off') 
def led1_off(): 
    GPIO.output(LED1, False) 
    return "LED1 Turned OFF" 
 
@app.route('/led2_on') 
def led2_on(): 
    GPIO.output(LED2, True) 
    return "LED2 Turned ON" 
 
@app.route('/led2_off') 
def led2_off(): 
    GPIO.output(LED2, False) 
    return "LED2 Turned OFF" 
if __name__ == '__main__': 
app.run(host='0.0.0.0') 

